Package com.rb.nonbiz.collections

Class ImmutableIndexableArray3D<X,​Y,​Z,​V>

java.lang.Object
com.rb.nonbiz.collections.ImmutableIndexableArray3D<X,​Y,​Z,​V>
public class ImmutableIndexableArray3D<X,​Y,​Z,​V>
extends java.lang.Object
Just like MutableIndexableArray3D, except immutable. Note that someone can modify the underlying object if they have a handle to it via getRawArrayUnsafe() but at least they can't modify it through THIS object; there's no set() method here. Plus, getRawArrayUnsafe is package-private, for extra safety.

    • filteredValuesStreamXYZ

      public java.util.stream.Stream<V> filteredValuesStreamXYZ​(Filter<X> xFilter, Filter<Y> yFilter, Filter<Z> zFilter)
      Returns values (in XYZ order), but not always all: for each dimension, if you specify a 'filter' (single value), then we'll only return that, otherwise we'll look at all values in each dimension. If all filters are Optional.empty, then it will return all values in XYZ order as a stream. I mean 'filter' as in 'database query select filter'. xFilter = Optional.of("a") means 'return all elements that have "a" in the x dimension. xFilter = Optional.empty() means "do not restrict / filter on the x dimension; return all items (that pass the other filters) without regard to their value in the x coordinate".
